The article is a statement issued on the 60th anniversary of the signing of the United States-Japan Treaty of Mutual Cooperation and Security. The statement congratulates and sends regards to Japanese and American leaders, including Prime Minister Shinzo Abe, Foreign Minister Toshimitsu Motegi, and Defense Minister Taro Kono. It emphasizes the importance of the strong alliance between the two nations in maintaining peace, security, and prosperity in the Indo-Pacific region and the world. The statement also highlights the need for further strengthening and deepening of the alliance in the face of evolving security challenges. It expresses confidence in Japan's continued contributions to mutual security and the thriving of the alliance in the future.